Mobile telecommunications firm Airtel Africa has reported a net profit of 408 million U.S dollars in it's latest trading results. The firm has enjoyed a rebound in it's east Africa business with its customer base rising by 11.9% to 110.6 million u.s dollars. airtel's revenue increased by 11.2% and the company's board has recommended a final dividend of 3 cents per share, to a total dividend of 6 cents per share.